stylometry: Goal Seek is used to find a solution when unsure of the starting value. Goal Seek solves one equation in one unknown. A Data Table is used to find a variety of solutions at all different levels by altering your original solution. Example: In problems in class, we changed the profit to 0, went to "What if Analysis" and created a data table. This was often used in problems that we were trying to maximize profit. I did this in the Jenniffer & Co. example when seeing the best way to maximizie profit at the salon by offering different services. It was interesting to see how much of a difference there was in profit, just by a slightly differnet amount of services given.
